  "curation": {
    "synopsis": "Acting on intelligence supplied by the captured Etogaur Mabbon, Gaunt proposes a deep-strike raid on Salvation's Reach — a fortress space hulk hidden in archenemy-held space that hosts Anarch Sek's strategic archive. If the data caches can be seized or destroyed, the Sek-vs-Innokenti civil war inside the Archenemy can be tipped in the Imperium's favour without a single battlefield engagement. The Tanith First — reinforced with fresh Verghastite and Belladon intakes for the assault — embarks on a small black-ops fleet under Captain Spika and pushes into deep Archenemy territory. The mission has a passenger: Felyx Chass, a teenage Verghastite intake who is in fact Merity Chass's child by Gaunt — the son Gaunt never knew he fathered. The raid itself is structured as a heist procedural through the Reach's twisted corridors against Blood Pact and emerging Sons of Sek defenders; the political subplot, with Mabbon's loyalty constantly in doubt and the Sirkle agents still hunting, runs parallel. Closes with the data in Imperial hands and the Victory arc proper opened.",
